&lt;p&gt;The Chief Architect for HealthShare is accountable for the architectural direction of the HealthShare platform and its evolution toward a more adoptable, upgradeable, and operationally efficient product. This role works across Development and Product Management to ensure architectural decisions support the product roadmap, improve execution across teams, and reduce the cost and complexity of deploying, upgrading, and operating HealthShare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role owns the long-term technical shape of the platform, including service boundaries, deployment architecture, tenancy model, operational model, interoperability architecture, and the standards needed to move HealthShare toward a more productized and manageable service platform. It is expected that key architectural directions will include multi-tenant-capable design, cloud-deployable services, and stronger operational manageability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role reports to the Director of Development, HealthCare Solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Accountability&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and maintain the target architecture for HealthShare.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive architectural evolution from deployment-specific patterns toward reusable platform services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure architectural investments materially reduce the cost and complexity of adoption, upgrade, and operation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide HealthShare services toward multi-tenant-capable, cloud-deployable, and operationally manageable designs where those approaches improve product scalability and lifecycle efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Align architecture with Product Management goals and roadmap priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and enforce architectural standards across teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor senior engineers and architects and raise the quality of technical decision-making across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set the architectural direction for HealthShare platform capabilities, shared services, and major subsystem investments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define platform architecture in ways that reduce implementation friction, simplify deployment, and improve upgrade consistency across customer environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead architecture for multi-tenancy, including tenant isolation, configuration strategy, security boundaries, data partitioning, and operational controls, where it supports lower-cost delivery and operation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define architectural requirements for cloud deployment, including portability, automation, resilience, observability, upgradeability, and lifecycle management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive improvements in manageability, including provisioning, deployment consistency, monitoring, telemetry, support diagnostics, and fault isolation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product Management to ensure architectural investments support product goals and avoid short-term decisions that increase downstream adoption, upgrade, or support cost.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide technical strategy for healthcare interoperability capabilities, including data exchange, transformation, normalization, orchestration, and standards alignment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review major technical designs and steer teams toward consistent platform patterns and reusable solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and drive reduction of technical debt that limits scalability, manageability, delivery speed, upgradeability, or product consistency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Influence roadmap sequencing where architectural prerequisites or technical constraints materially affect delivery, operational efficiency, or customer lifecycle cost.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build alignment across teams when technical tradeoffs span product, architecture, delivery, support, and operational concerns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&g

&lt;p&gt;Clinical Advisor&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location - Windsor/ Edinburgh, UK&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Type of Work - Office&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Role Overview&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Clinical Advisor will provide clinical guidance for the strategic planning, management, integration, and implementation of health information systems related to InterSystems products. Working closely with Sales, Implementation, Product and support teams. the Clinical Advisor will play a key role throughout the sales lifecycle, helping prospective and existing customers understand how InterSystems solutions address clinical, operational, and strategic healthcare challenges.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role requires understanding of the InterSystems product portfolio and the ability to effectively articulate product value to executive, clinical, and operational stakeholders. The Clinical Advisor will lead and support customer presentations, workshops, product demonstrations,&amp;nbsp; translating clinical requirements into compelling solution narratives that align with customer objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Clinical Advisor will develop and maintain strong relationships with executive leadership, including C-suite executives and senior clinical leaders across the UK healthcare market, acting as a trusted advisor to promote excellence in healthcare through the adoption and optimisation of InterSystems solutions. The individual will contribute to business development activities, support strategic account planning, influence purchasing decisions, and provide clinical expertise during procurement, implementation, and transformation initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow trends in Healthcare Analytics, Evidence Based Medicine, Clinical Quality Measures, Accountable Care and Clinical Decision Support and advise Executive leadership and product development teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Play a key role in procurement and bid processes, from opportunity qualification and requirements gathering through to proposal development, customer presentations, and product demonstrations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide strategic insight/guidance on behalf of InterSystems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review healthcare informatics trends, experiences and approaches. Advise healthcare organisations on how health information solutions can address their challenges and support their clinical, operational, and transformation goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide healthcare technology expertise to product, sales and marketing management teams to ensure the successful positioning of industry solutions and go to market tactics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide market-driven information for product strategy and development direction using industry expertise and direct interaction with customers, prospects, analysts, and other external resources&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent InterSystems to Clinical societies, advocacy groups and Clinical advisory boards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver the InterSystems strategy to senior leader and peers in the UK Healthcare market&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct strategic issues, investment or partnering decisions, and actions regarding key regulatory demands and requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide clinical and product input to all InterSystems and customer teams including Delivery, Product, and support to increase clinical knowledge and adoption&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Experience/Qualification Required &lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess strong grasp of clinical workflow in either community, acute or mental health settings, interest in health information systems and outcomes measurement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A contemporary clinician who understands major trends in healthcare and man

&lt;div&gt;The Clinical Application Specialist will use their healthcare, business and InterSystems product knowledge to ensure that we contract and implement InterSystems products in a successful, standard and timely manner. &amp;nbsp;The Application Specialist will become an “expert” Nursing/ Doctor/Midwife resource for customers and will be expected to understand the customer process, assess solution best fit and advise the customer how to best implement the standard solution as early as possible. &amp;nbsp;Advise the customer on driving maximum benefits from the solution, whilst keeping customer specific work to an absolute minimum and liaise with various areas of the business on these accordingly. It is therefore essential, that they keep up to date with new product developments as they become available through the normal product release cycle. &amp;nbsp;The Clinical Application Specialist must be available to visit customer sites and may be assigned to projects that require regular travel with the possibility of spending up to 5 days away from home each week.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;The Application Specialist will act in accordance with the latest version of the InterSystems ARIES Customer Engagement Methodology, which will be modified from time to time as part of our ongoing culture of continuous improvement. &amp;nbsp;The Application Specialist will undertake the following:&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Discovery&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;•     Review proposal and tender documentation prior to release to customer and inform colleagues on gaps in areas of functionality&lt;/div&gt;
